Ask HN: Do you like to centralize your notes/bookmarks/etc.?
text:
On one end we have the centralized "Everything in one place" approach, whether it's done semi-automatically with a smart-app or manually in a digital/physical commonplace notebook. And on the other end we have the context/technology-specific bookmarks, saves, highlights, etc. dispersed throughout various places.

The former often seems more organized, though it's hard to implement well, takes a lot of work, and often misses out on context. The latter is often the default, baked-in option, but when there's many sources it can feel very scattered.

Where do you sit on this spectrum? What's your strategy to managing information from various sources?
